
This checklist helps us test CSwitch in a thorough manner by keeping track of all the unique bits of functionality that we think could experience regressions between versions
By following this list slowly and methodically we can test the majority of major code-paths in CSwitch on each platform to make sure things are working as expected
A major bug fix or change while we're performing a test should cause an restart of the list, since unintended consequences of a change might cause another feature to break
This checklist should be run on every platform before every release. Upon successful completion on each platform we should save and label that binary as the official version
Whenever bugs (especially regressions) are encountered in regular testing we should add items to this list to help track them in the future
As new features are added, or existing features are changed, this list should be expanded or modified to reflect those changes
We should track how long each test takes, once we get to 10+ minutes of testing on a single platform, even once practiced, we should prioritize certain tests over others

