# Checklist (Should be performed once on each platform)
	[ ] Change build_config.h: BUILD_INTO_SINGLE_UNIT, BUNDLE_RESOURCES, USE_BUNDLED_RESOURCES, !DEBUG_BUILD, BUILD_SHADERS, !PROFILING_ENABLED
	[ ] Compile the executable, move it to the Programs folder (or any empty folder), check to make sure it has executable permissions, start the program from explorer
	[ ] Drag and drop to open file
	[ ] F6 to open framerate graph, make sure the framerate is reasonable
	[ ] File -> Open File (also test Ctrl+O)
	[ ] Ctrl+Tab and Ctrl+Shift+Tab to change tabs
	[ ] Ctrl+W and Middle Click to close file, Ctrl+E to re-open file(s)
	[ ] Reset file (Confirm dialog should work properly, try Cancel as well!)
	[ ] Close all files
	[ ] Open Recent File, restart CSwitch to make sure it's persisting
	[ ] Clear Recent Files
	[ ] Delete "%APPDATA%/Roaming/C_Switch/" or "~/.C_Switch" and start CSwitch
	[ ] For EACH setting, change through menu AND hotkey, check functionality changes, checking "settings.txt" and restarting application to make sure it persists properly
		[ ] Light Mode (F9)
		[ ] Small Buttons (F10)
		[ ] Topmost (Ctrl+T) //Windows only, shouldn't persist, Linux has an option if you right-click on window title
		[ ] Clip Names on Right
		[ ] Smooth Scrolling
		[ ] Option Tooltips
		[ ] Topbar (F11 and ESC) //shouldn't persist
		[ ] Custom Theme (open, light/dark mode, restart, clear, and try opening invalid theme)
	[ ] Make sure tooltips show up on all things and are not missing characters or incorrectly formatted/possitioned
	[ ] Ctrl+Plus/Minus, Ctrl+Scroll and Ctrl+0 to scale UI (to max and min scale, shouldn't crash, shouldn't horrendously fail to layout)
	[ ] PageUp/PageDown and Home/End to scroll up/down with keyboard
	[ ] Click and drag scrollbar
	[ ] Click in scroll gutter to jump up/down to a particular position
	[ ] Arrow Up/Down to move keyboard selection. Enter to toggle options.
	[ ] Hold Down to rapidly move to options (shouldn't loop around the end/beginning unless you repress the arrow key)
	[ ] Does application icon show properly in File Explorer and in taskbar?
	[ ] Does window title change when opening different files and changing tabs?
	[ ] Maximize and Minimize application, shouldn't crash or cause any issues
	[ ] Make the window large, open a file with a lot of options, and check framerate with F6
	[ ] Make the window small (test recent files submenu when window is skinny)
	[ ] Check CPU usage of application while idle
	[ ] Ellipses on file path in topbar should be placed appropriately (in the middle of the folder portion of the path, prioritizing the file name)
	[ ] Shortened names in recent files dialog should be distinguishable (just enough to be unique), and tooltips should be readable (full path)
	[ ] Check 0/1 defines work
	[ ] Check true/false defines work
	[ ] Check commentable defines work
	[ ] Open an empty file
	[ ] Open a binary or large file
	[ ] Open a file that has spaces in the path
	[ ] Change the file on disk while it's open in CSwitch
	[ ] Open multiple instances of CSwitch
		[ ] Open a new file, check "recent_files.txt" is automatically reloaded in other instance
		[ ] Check that "settings.txt" are not auto-reloaded, and last changer wins for all options
	[ ] Lock the computer while CSwitch is running, and then sign back in, shouldn't crash or cause graphical issues
	[ ] On Laptop: Try changing desktops rapidly until the graphics driver crashes?
	[ ] Pass a file path on the command-line as an argument
	[ ] Pass an invalid file path on the command-line as an argument
	[ ] Pass a file path with quotes on the command-line as an argument (ideally one with spaces that would warrant the quotes)
	[ ] Pass the "-size=300,600" argument (and "-top" on Windows)
